    and <inline-formula><alternatives>
    <tex-math><![CDATA[j]]></tex-math>
    <mml:math display="inline" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>,
    respectively. Additionally, <inline-formula><alternatives>
    <tex-math><![CDATA[e_{k}]]></tex-math>
    <mml:math display="inline" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>,
    <inline-formula><alternatives>
    <tex-math><![CDATA[e_{i}]]></tex-math>
    <mml:math display="inline" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>,
    and <inline-formula><alternatives>
    <tex-math><![CDATA[e_{r_{i}}]]></tex-math>
    <mml:math display="inline" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>r</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:msub></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>
    are the judges, units and sub-units idiosyncratic deviations.
    Lastly, <inline-formula><alternatives>
    <tex-math><![CDATA[O_{kijr_{ij}}]]></tex-math>
    <mml:math display="inline" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mml:msub><mml:mi>O</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>r</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>
    describes the dichotomous <italic>observed</italic> outcome.</p>
    <p>Following what it is stated by the DAG, we can transform it into
    an SCM, in the following way</p>
    <p><styled-content id="eq-StructuralModel"><disp-formula><tex-math><![CDATA[
    \begin{aligned}
      O_{kijr_{ij}} := & \; f_{O}( \delta_{kijr_{ij}} ) \\
      \delta_{kijr_{ij}} := & \; f_{D}( \gamma_{k}, \theta_{ir_{i}} ) \\
      \gamma_{k} := & \; f_{G}( Z_{k}, e_{k} ) \\
      \theta_{ir_{i}} := & \; f_{R}( \theta_{i}, Y_{r}, e_{r_{i}} ) \\
      \theta_{i} := & \; f_{T}( X_{i}, e_{i} ) \\
      & \; e_{k} \perp\kern-5pt\perp e_{i} \\
      & \; e_{k} \perp\kern-5pt\perp e_{r_{i}} \\
      & \; e_{i} \perp\kern-5pt\perp e_{r_{i}}
    \end{aligned}
     \qquad(1)]]></tex-math></disp-formula></styled-content></p>
  </sec>
